OL,3,C'The truth has come out' - former sub
OL,4,Cpostmaster says scandal ruined his life
OL,6,F"Today, we apologise unreservedly for
OL,7,Fthe suffering which Post Office caused
OL,8,Fto postmasters and their loved ones.
OL,9,FWe will carefully consider the report
OL,10,Fand its recommendations."
OL,12,FThe government is expected to give is
OL,13,Fa statement in the House of Commons
OL,14,Flater on Tuesday.
OL,16,FPost Office Minister, Gareth Thomas,
OL,17,Fsaid: "I welcome the Inquiry's
OL,18,Fpublication today and pay tribute to
OL,19,FSir Wyn and his team for their
OL,20,Fcomprehensive and penetrating work.
